Module HW08
Package provided.mixedData

Interface IMixedDataDictionary

All Known Implementing Classes:
MixedDataDictionary
public interface IMixedDataDictionary
Abstract mixed data dictionary interface A mixed data dictionary can hold multiple value types and retrieve those values in a type-safe manner. The use of a MixedDataKey is required as this special key carries typing information. This guarantees that the type of the values associated with the key match the type specified by the key. Thus, no casting of the value returned by a "get" operation is necessary.
Author:
swong

    • containsKey

      boolean containsKey​(MixedDataKey<?> key)
      Check if the dictionary contains a value for the given key
      Parameters:
      key - The key to check
      Returns:
      true if a value exists in the dictionary for the given key, false otherwise.

    • put

      <T> T put​(MixedDataKey<T> key, T value)
      Put a value into the dictionary, associated with the given key, replacing any value already in the dictionary that is already associated with the key. The type of the value must be a that or a subclass of that specified by the key.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of data being put in
      Parameters:
      key - the key to use to find the value
      value - The value to associate with the key
      Returns:
      The previous value associated with the key or null if there was none.

    • get

      <T> T get​(MixedDataKey<T> key)
      Get the value associated with the given key
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of data being retrieved
      Parameters:
      key - the key to use
      Returns:
      The value associated with the key or null if there is no entry for the key. The returned value is properly typed to the expected type so no casting is required.
